'\" t
.TH "RECovery INIT" "8" "" "recinit"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------
.SH "NAME"
recinit - \fBRec\fRovery \fBInit\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.B recinit
is a script that runs as root, to provide a recovery shell on systems
without VTs. It starts an instance of the wlroots-based wayland server
.BR cage (1)
which starts the
.BR foot (1)
terminal emulator, which then starts an applicable command.
.SH "STARTUP AND USAGE"
.B recinit
can be run at early system startup by specifying
.B init=/bin/recinit
on the kernel command line.
.PP
.B recinit
also starts when the initrd fails. As of now, there are initrd hooks
for
.BR dracut (8),
.BR mkinitcpio (8),
and
.BR initramfs-tools (7)
that install the needed files for
.B recinit
to run, as well as intercept the initrd panic routine so that instead
of trying to start the shell, it starts
.B recinit
instead, provided that there are no VTs. The panic routine is run
typically by the initrd system when it fails to mount the rootfs, or
an option like
.B break=top
is specified to the kernel. (This example is for
.B initramfs-tools
initrds.)
.PP
.B recinit
also starts when
.BR systemd (1)
hits the
.B emergency
or
.B rescue
targets.
.PP
.B recinit
is not typically manually invoked by users, except for the
.B init=/bin/recinit
option.
.SH "ACCESSIBILITY"
.B recinit
supports an optional accessible mode, where all the text is
read by the fenrir screen reader.
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
.B @sysconfdir@/vtty/kanshiconfig.conf
is the configuration file for a small daemon that ensures that
.BR cage (1)
uses clone mode.
.PP
By creating a
.B @sysconfdir@/vtty/accessiblemode
file. (it can be empty), enables the accessible mode.
.PP
.B @sysconfdir@/vtty/footkiosk.conf
is the configuration for the
.BR foot (1)
terminal emulator.
.PP
The directory
.B @sysconfdir@/vtty/
is set as
.B $XDG_CONFIG_HOME
so that any other library configuration files, like
.B ~/.config/xkb
can be set by an administrator.
.SH "BOOT OPTIONS"
.IP \[bu]
.B vconsole.xkblayout=
.RS 12
Sets
.B XKBLAYOUT
for recinit.
.RE
.IP \[bu]
.B vconsole.xkbmodel=
.RS 12
Sets
.B XKBMODEL
for recinit.
.RE
.IP \[bu]
.B vconsole.xkbvariant=
.RS 12
Sets
.B XKBVARIANT
for recinit.
.RE
.IP \[bu]
.B vconsole.xkboptions=
.RS 12
Sets
.B XKBOPTIONS
for recinit.
.RE
.IP \[bu]
.B vttyaccessible
.RS 12
Enables accessibility mode for recinit. 
.RE
.IP \[bu]
.B novttyaccessible
.RS 12
Disables accessibility mode for recinit. This always takes precedence
so that in case there is a problem with
.BR fenrir (1)
the system is not unusable.
.RE
.SH NOTES
Only the first GPU in the seat is used. Recinit will not span to
screens on the second card.

